Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your potatoes. Cut the @New Potatoes{350%g} into eighths and cook in the water for around ~{7%minutes} (until just tender). Drain and allow to cool slightly.

> Don't overcook the potatoes as you will cook them again with the chorizo.

Peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peeled and chopped into 1cm cubes).

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a #non-stick pan{}. Add the @Diced Chorizo{1/4%cup} and cook over a medium heat for ~{2%minutes} to allow the oil to be released.

Add the onions and potatoes to the pan. Add the leaves of the @Thyme{3%sprigs} and @salt{1/2%tsp} and a few grinds of @Pepper{a few grinds}. Cook over a medium heat for around ~{8%minutes} or until everything has crisped up a bit.

> If you happen to have some flour in the cupboard you can use it for crispier fish. Simply mix 2 tbsp of plain flour with a good pinch of salt and pepper. Coat the fish thoroughly in the flour before moving to the next step.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in another non-stick pan over a medium-high heat. Season the @Tilapia Fillet{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add to the pan and cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Very gently turn the fillets over and immediately take off the heat, allowing the residual heat from the pan to cook the flesh for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Wild Rocket{1%handful} through the sautéed potatoes and serve topped with the seared tilapia fillets. Get. Stuck. In.